add("ITGC-AC-15","ITGC · Access","ITGC","All","A compromised or shared session cannot be terminated — a stolen/forwarded JWT stays valid for its full lifetime, and a deactivated user's existing token keeps working, so there is no incident-containment kill-switch.","Restricted access",
    "Session revocation: JWTs carry a jti so a session can be killed before expiry. Logout adds the token's jti to a denylist (revoked_tokens) which the global auth guard checks every request; an admin can revoke ALL of a user's sessions (users.tokens_valid_from watermark — any JWT issued before it is rejected) for incident response; and account DEACTIVATION is enforced live (the guard re-checks is_active each request, so a disabled account's token stops working immediately rather than lasting up to 8h). (Brute-force login lockout is a tracked follow-on.)","Prev","Automated","Continuous","Eng Lead / Security","P11",
    "auth.service.ts revokeToken/revokeAllSessions (+ jti on issued JWTs); auth.controller.ts (auth/logout revokes jti, auth/users/:username/revoke-sessions); common/guards.ts (jti-denylist + is_active + tokens_valid_from checks); schema/users.ts revoked_tokens + users.tokens_valid_from + migration 0144; cutover/compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the jti-denylist + revoke-all watermark + the guard's per-request revocation/deactivation checks.","Re-perform: log in, logout → the token is rejected (TOKEN_REVOKED); deactivate an account → its existing token is rejected (USER_DEACTIVATED); revoke-all → pre-existing tokens rejected (re-performed by the harness).","Revocation denylist + SoD/deactivation test","Implemented")
add("ITGC-AC-16","ITGC · Access","ITGC","All","The primary financial audit trail is append-only but not tamper-EVIDENT — immutability is enforced only by a DB trigger it shares a trust boundary with, so a superuser (or out-of-band DB access) bypassing the trigger could alter/delete history undetectably.","Completeness/Integrity",
    "Audit hash chain (tamper-evidence): every audit_log row carries a per-(tenant) monotonic seq + prev_hash + hash, each hash binding the previous hash + the row's content (actor/tenant/action/ip/request_id/status/meta) — exactly the pos_journal (ITGC-AC-11) construction. The append is serialised by a FOR UPDATE lock on the latest row so concurrent writes can't fork the chain. Re-walking the chain (GET /api/admin/audit/verify, gated by 'users', RLS-scoped) recomputes every hash and reports the first row where the sequence gaps or a hash mismatches — so ANY edit/delete/insert of a past row (even one that bypassed the append-only trigger) is DETECTED. Complements ITGC-AC-10 (immutability) with detectability.","Det","Automated","Continuous / on verify","Eng Lead / Security","P13/P16",
    "common/audit.interceptor.ts (auditRowHash + per-tenant FOR UPDATE chain append); audit-viewer.service.ts verifyChain + audit-viewer.controller.ts (GET /api/admin/audit/verify); schema/system.ts audit_log.seq/prev_hash/hash + migration 0148; cutover/compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the chain construction (seq + prev_hash + content hash, FOR UPDATE serialisation) + the verify walk.","Re-perform: verify returns ok over the accumulated chain; then alter a past row behind a DISABLEd append-only trigger and re-verify → ok=false with a hash mismatch at the tampered seq (re-performed by the harness).","Chain verify (intact + tamper-detected) test","Implemented")
add("ITGC-AC-17","ITGC · Access","ITGC","Revenue / Cash","A fast front-of-house PIN login could become a back door — a short, shared or guessable PIN, or a PIN assigned to a privileged account, would let a 4–6 digit code bypass the password + MFA controls that gate financial functions.","Restricted access",
    "POS-PIN quick-login is scoped to LOW-PRIVILEGE tills only: a per-user PIN is scrypt-hashed (never stored in clear; same KDF as the password) and any role whose effective permissions require MFA is HARD-BLOCKED from both SETTING and USING a PIN — the second factor can't be downgraded to a 4–6 digit code. PIN login shares the ITGC-AC-07 per-account lockout (a PIN brute-force trips the same throttle), set/rotate is step-up-gated (self: re-enter current password; admin: 'users' access-admin authority), and the combined 'login + เปิดกะ' action still gates opening a cash shift on pos_till (SoD R08) — a plain cashier only signs in.","Prev","Automated","Per login / on-demand","IT Security / Store Ops","P11",
    "auth.service.ts loginWithPin (lockout + privileged block + scrypt verify) / setOwnPin / setPinFor / clearPinFor (assertPinAllowed); auth.controller.ts (POST /api/login/pin, /api/auth/me/pin, POST+DELETE /api/auth/users/:username/pin); password.service.ts (scrypt KDF reused); permissions.ts requiresMfa; schema/users.ts pin_hash/pin_set_at + migration 0181; payments.controller.ts till/current; cutover/pos-pin.ts (ToE)","Inspect that the PIN is hashed (not clear), that a privileged role can neither set nor use a PIN, the shared lockout, and the step-up on set/rotate.","Re-perform: cashier PIN login → 200 (+ permissions); wrong PIN → 401; a privileged account with a valid PIN → 401 PIN_NOT_ALLOWED; self set-PIN requires the current password; admin set-PIN refused for a privileged target; clearing a PIN disables PIN login (re-performed by the pos-pin harness).","POS-PIN restriction ToE (pos-pin)","Implemented")

# ---- Privacy: PDPA (Thailand Personal Data Protection Act) ----
add("PDPA-01","Privacy · PDPA","ITGC","All","A data subject's rights request (access / rectification / portability / objection / erasure) is not tracked or is missed past the 30-day statutory deadline — a PDPA compliance + reputational exposure.","Completeness/Timeliness",
    "DSAR register + workflow: POST /api/pdpa/dsar files a request (subject_type member/customer/employee/user x request_type access/rectification/erasure/portability/objection), stamped with the statutory 30-day due_date and a status lifecycle (received->in_progress->completed/rejected). Access/portability is fulfilled by POST /api/pdpa/dsar/:id/export which assembles the subject's data bundle (profile + per-purpose consents + points ledger) and closes the request; reject records a reason. Gated by 'users' (the DPO/AccessAdmin duty, same as the access review + audit viewer) and tenant-scoped by RLS (a tenant sees only its own requests).","Det","Automated","Per request / within 30 days","DPO / AccessAdmin","P16",
    "pdpa/pdpa.service.ts (createDsar sets 30-day due_date; exportSubject bundles profile+consents+ledger; listDsar/getDsar/rejectDsar); pdpa/pdpa.controller.ts (/api/pdpa/dsar*, perm 'users'); schema/pdpa.ts dsar_requests + migration 0180 (RLS); cutover/pdpa.ts (ToE)","Inspect the DSAR lifecycle, the 30-day due-date stamp, the export bundle contents, and the RLS scoping.","Re-perform: file an access DSAR (received + ~30-day due), export (profile/consents/ledger returned, completed), reject (rejected); a DPO in another tenant cannot read the request (404) - re-performed by the pdpa harness.","DSAR register + 30-day SLA test","Implemented")
add("PDPA-02","Privacy · PDPA","ITGC","All","Honouring erasure (right to be forgotten) conflicts with the immutable, hash-chained financial audit trail (ITGC-AC-10/AC-16): deleting/editing audit rows to remove PII would break tamper-evidence, yet leaving PII in place violates PDPA.","Confidentiality/Integrity",
    "Erasure with read-time pseudonymisation: POST /api/pdpa/dsar/:id/erase redacts the subject's PII in the operational store (pos_members name/phone/email/card/LINE nulled, consents withdrawn, account deactivated - id + member_code kept for referential integrity) and records an append-only pdpa_erasures ledger row (subject + erased PII values + a stable pseudonym). The audit_log itself is NEVER mutated - its bytes and hash chain stay intact - instead the audit viewer/exports apply the ledger at READ time, replacing any erased PII with the pseudonym. So PDPA erasure and audit tamper-evidence both hold simultaneously.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per erasure request","DPO / AccessAdmin","P16",
    "pdpa/pdpa.service.ts (eraseSubject redacts pos_members + withdraws consents + writes pdpa_erasures; maskAuditRows applies the ledger); audit-viewer.service.ts (query/exportCsv call maskAuditRows); schema/pdpa.ts pdpa_erasures + migration 0180 (RLS); cutover/pdpa.ts (ToE)","Inspect that erasure redacts the source PII, records the pseudonym ledger, and that the stored audit row is unchanged while views mask it.","Re-perform: erase a member -> PII redacted (name=[erased], phone null) + pseudonym issued; the audit viewer shows the pseudonym (no PII) while the raw stored audit row still contains the original PII (immutability preserved) - re-performed by the pdpa harness.","Erasure + audit pseudonymisation test","Implemented")

