add("REV-12","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable","Overdue receivables not pursued; collection lapses; further credit extended to a defaulting customer.","Valuation/Authorization",
    "AR collections worklist + escalating dunning ladder (reminder→legal) recorded per invoice (DUN-), with the per-stage notice DISPATCHED to the customer (email/SMS/LINE via the messaging gateway; delivery outcome + recipient logged); credit-status / credit-check hold (over-limit OR 90+ days overdue). The serious-overdue hold is ENFORCED at POS/portal order entry (CREDIT_OVERDUE) under the FOR-UPDATE tenant lock, single-sourced with the collections on_hold threshold so the two never drift.","Det/Prev","Auto+Manual","Per overdue invoice / per order","AR / Controller","P10/P16",
    "collections.service.ts (worklist, recordDunning+dispatch, runDunningSweep, creditStatus, creditCheck, SERIOUS_OVERDUE_DAYS); messaging.service.ts (notice delivery); pos.service.ts (createOrder CREDIT_OVERDUE); collections.controller.ts (incl. cron-callable /collections/sweep); bi.service.ts (ar_collections_dunning scheduled job, daily via runDue); /finance Collections UI; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect aging→stage logic, notice dispatch, hold decision, automated+scheduled sweep + order-entry gate.","Worklist ages open AR; manual + automated (idempotent) + daily-scheduled dunning recorded AND the notice delivered (message_log, channel auto-picked from contact); held customer's credit-check denied; a 90+ defaulter is blocked at order entry while a good-standing customer orders (re-performed by the harness).","Dunning log + message_log; sweep/scheduler run log; credit-hold report; CREDIT_OVERDUE rejections","Implemented")
add("REV-13","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash","Cash over/short never hits the books, or a cashier clears their own material drawer discrepancy — a shortage (theft/skimming) is buried because book-cash (1000) is never reconciled to the physical count, and no independent review gates a large variance.","Accuracy/Completeness/Authorization",
    "Till-close cash over/short GL posting + material-variance maker-checker (SoD): on closeTill the variance (counted − expected) is POSTED to GL — short → Dr 5830 Cash Over/Short / Cr 1000 Cash; over → Dr 1000 / Cr 5830 — so the cash control account always tracks the physical count (idempotent per till via source=TILL_CLOSE). A variance at/above the materiality threshold (THB 100) posts the over/short as a DRAFT JE and parks the session in PendingApproval: a DIFFERENT user (manager) must approve (POST /api/payments/till/variance/:sessionNo/approve) before it is effective — self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION (binds even Admin); reject voids the draft. Sub-threshold variances post immediately. The till still closes either way (the cash has left the drawer); only the GL clearing of a material discrepancy is gated.","Prev/Det","Automated","Per shift close","Store Ops Mgr / Controller","P10/P16",
    "payments.service.ts (closeTill posts 5830↔1000, approveVariance/rejectVariance via ledger.approveEntry/rejectEntry SoD); payments.controller.ts (till/variance/:sessionNo/approve|reject, pos_till); schema/payments.ts till_sessions.variance_status/variance_journal_no + migration 0140 (account 5830); ledger COA 5830 Cash Over/Short; cutover/cashreport.ts (ToE)","Inspect the over/short JE direction + the materiality gate + the approver≠closer check + that a material variance posts a Draft (excluded from balances) until approved.","Re-perform: close with a small short → over/short posts to 5830 immediately (NotRequired); close with a material short → Draft JE + PendingApproval, self-approve blocked (SOD_VIOLATION), a different user approves → JE Posted; trial balance stays balanced throughout (re-performed by the cashreport harness).","Cash over/short JEs (5830); till variance approval trail","Implemented")
add("POS-07","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash; Revenue","The close-of-day Z-tape can be altered after the fact — a shift's recorded sales/cash totals are mutated to conceal skimming, and there is no immutable, attested record an auditor can rely on to prove the day's takings as originally counted.","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Signed, tamper-evident Z-report archive (POS-07): closing a till computes the shift totals (gross sales, by-method, expected vs counted cash, over/short — see REV-13); a manager then SIGNS the Z-report (POST /api/payments/till/:sessionNo/z-report/sign, gated pos_close — distinct from the cashier's pos_till) which SNAPSHOTS those totals + the denomination count into an immutable record (xz_reports/xz_report_denominations) carrying a content_hash = sha256 over the canonical totals. Signing is only allowed once the till is Closed (TILL_NOT_CLOSED otherwise) and is idempotent per till (a second sign returns the existing record — no duplicate Z-tape). On read, the stored hash is RE-COMPUTED from the persisted totals and any mismatch is surfaced as hash_valid=false, so a later edit to the archived row is detectable. A sell-only Cashier (pos_sell) cannot sign — the attestation is a manager duty.","Det","Automated","Per shift close","Store Ops Mgr / Controller","P10/P16",
    "payments.service.ts (signZReport snapshots aggregateTill totals + denominations, content_hash via node:crypto, idempotent per till; getXzReport recomputes the hash → hash_valid; listXzReports); payments.controller.ts (till/:sessionNo/z-report/sign pos_close, xz-reports[/:id]); schema/payments.ts xz_reports + xz_report_denominations + migration 0157; permissions.ts pos_close (PosSupervisor); cutover/cashreport.ts (ToE)","Inspect the sign→SIGNED+content_hash flow, the closed-till precondition, the idempotency, and the hash recompute → hash_valid tamper flag.","Re-perform: close a till, sign the Z (SIGNED + 64-hex hash, denominations snapshotted), re-sign (already=true, same hash), fetch (hash_valid=true), tamper a persisted total (hash_valid=false), sign an open till (TILL_NOT_CLOSED), Cashier sign (403) — re-performed by the cashreport harness.","Signed Z-report archive + tamper-detection test","Implemented")
add("REV-14","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable; Bad-debt expense","An uncollectible receivable is written off the books without independent review — one person both declares the receivable uncollectible and posts the write-off, concealing a misappropriated customer collection (lapping) or removing a still-collectible balance.","Valuation/Authorization",
    "AR bad-debt write-off maker-checker (SoD): POST /api/finance/ar/write-off books the write-off (Dr 5720 Bad Debt Expense / Cr 1100 AR) as a DRAFT via the ledger maker-checker (GL-05) — excluded from the trial balance until a DIFFERENT user approves it (POST /api/ledger/journal/:entryNo/approve); a self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION (binds even Admin), and the pending write-off surfaces in the pending-approvals monitor automatically (it is a Draft JE). A non-positive amount → BAD_AMOUNT and a missing reason is rejected. The write-off register (GET /api/finance/ar/write-offs) lists every write-off Draft(pending)/Posted(approved)/Voided(rejected) with its amount for controller review.","Prev","Automated","Per write-off","AR / Controller","P10",
    "finance.service.ts writeOffAr/listWriteOffs; finance.controller.ts (ar/write-off, ar/write-offs); ledger COA 5720 Bad Debt Expense; reuses ledger.approveEntry maker-checker (GL-05); cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the write-off → Draft (excluded from balances) → approve flow + the approver≠maker check + that nothing posts until approval.","Re-perform: request a write-off (Draft, 5720 unchanged), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user; confirm 5720 bad-debt expense + 1100 relief only after approval; the register lists it (re-performed by the basics harness).","Write-off register + SoD test","Implemented")
add("REV-15","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable; Revenue","No single customer-of-record — B2C loyalty members and B2B accounts live in disjoint silos, so revenue-by-customer, a 360 view, and AR-by-customer cannot be reconciled to one identity (incomplete/duplicated customer reporting; AR mis-attributed).","Completeness/Accuracy",
    "Unified customer master: a single registry (customer_master) is the customer-of-record, LINKING the pre-existing silos — member_id → pos_members (B2C loyalty) and account_code → the B2B customer tenant (orders + AR) — without disturbing them. A 360 view (GET /api/customer-master/:no/360) joins both: loyalty tier/points + the B2B orders/stats and AR balance, and the 360 AR-outstanding TIES to the AR sub-ledger for that account (revenue/AR resolve to one record). Tenant-scoped (RLS). Create/link/search are gated by crm/exec/ar.","Det","Auto+Manual","Continuous / per customer","CRM / AR / Controller","P13",
    "customers.module.ts CustomerMasterService (create/list/get/link/view360 — reuses CustomersService.detail for the B2B side); customer-master controller (POST/GET /api/customer-master, :no/360, :no/link); schema/customer-master.ts customer_master + migration 0149; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the master registry + the 360 join across loyalty + AR + that 360 AR-outstanding ties to the AR sub-ledger.","Re-perform: create a customer-of-record linking a B2B account + a B2C member; GET 360 → loyalty tier/points present and AR-outstanding equals the AR sub-ledger for the account; search finds the record (re-performed by the basics harness).","Customer master register + 360 AR tie-out","Implemented")
add("REV-16","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash; Revenue","A cashier issues a large refund without any independent review — refunding to themselves/an accomplice or reversing a real sale to skim the cash (refund fraud), because the refund moves money the moment one person requests it.","Authorization/Occurrence",
    "Refund maker-checker (SoD): a STANDALONE refund (POST /api/payments/refunds) at/above the materiality threshold (THB 1,000) is parked as a REQUEST (refund_requests) and MOVES NO MONEY — no payment_refunds row, the payment is not flipped — until a DIFFERENT user approves it (POST /api/payments/refund-requests/:id/approve); self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION; reject voids the request. Sub-threshold refunds run immediately, and a refund that is part of a goods-return is never gated (the return is the authorizing document, REV-07). The pending request auto-surfaces in the GOV-01 pending-approvals monitor and an inline approve/reject sits on the /approvals screen. The over-refund guard (REV-06) still binds at execution.","Prev","Automated","Per large refund","PosSupervisor / Controller","P10",
    "payments.service.ts refund (threshold gate → requestRefund), approveRefund/rejectRefund (SoD by username), listRefundRequests; payments.controller.ts (refund-requests/:id/approve|reject, pos_refund/ar/exec); schema/payments.ts refund_requests + migration 0151; finance.pendingApprovals (GOV-01 9th source); /approvals inline action; cutover/refund-approval.ts (ToE)","Inspect the threshold gate, the request-posts-nothing property, the approver≠requester check, and that the goods-return path is not gated.","Re-perform: a small refund runs immediately; a large refund parks PendingApproval (no payment_refunds row) + surfaces in GOV-01; self-approve → SOD_VIOLATION; a different user approves → the refund executes; reject moves no money (re-performed by the refund-approval harness).","Refund-request worklist + SoD test","Implemented")
add("REV-17","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue (pipeline / forecast)","Sales pipeline ungoverned — no lead-to-opportunity motion or controlled stage progression, so the revenue forecast is unreliable (opportunities skip stages, closed deals are silently re-opened, lost deals carry no reason), and converted leads don't attach to a customer-of-record.","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "CRM sales pipeline on the customer-of-record: leads → qualify → CONVERT (creates/attaches a customer_master + an opportunity; a converted/lost lead can't be re-converted) → opportunities run a controlled stage machine (prospecting/qualification/proposal/negotiation/won/lost) where won/lost are TERMINAL (a closed opportunity can't be re-staged → OPP_CLOSED) and lost REQUIRES a reason (LOST_REASON_REQUIRED). The weighted pipeline forecast = Σ open-opportunity amount × probability (probability tracks the stage), with won/lost totals + win-rate — the revenue forecast finance relies on. Activities (call/email/meeting/note/task) are logged per lead/opportunity. Tenant-scoped (RLS); gated crm/exec/ar.","Det","Auto+Manual","Continuous / per deal","CRM / Sales / Controller","P13",
    "crm-pipeline.service.ts (createLead/qualifyLead/convertLead/loseLead, createOpportunity/setStage stage-machine, pipelineSummary weighted forecast, logActivity); crm-pipeline.controller.ts (/api/crm/pipeline/*); schema/crm-pipeline.ts crm_leads/crm_opportunities/crm_activities + migration 0152; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the lead-conversion → customer-of-record link + the opportunity stage machine (won/lost terminal, lost-reason required) + the weighted forecast.","Re-perform: create a lead, qualify, convert (→ CUS- + OPP-, re-convert blocked), advance the opportunity to won (terminal — re-stage blocked), lost without a reason blocked; the weighted forecast + won total compute; activities log/list (re-performed by the basics harness).","Pipeline stage-machine + weighted forecast test","Implemented")
add("TIP-01","Revenue & Cash","Application","Cash; Tips Payable (2300)","Staff tips are skimmed or mis-paid — tips collected from guests are never paid out (the 2300 liability grows unexplained), more is paid out than was collected (theft via inflated tip-outs), or the cashier who rings sales also pays the tips (to self).","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Tip pooling / distribution with SoD: tips ride into 2300 Tips Payable on checkout (a staff pass-through liability, not revenue/VAT). A distribution (POST /api/restaurant/tips/distribute) pays the pooled tips out to staff for a period — Dr 2300 / Cr 1000 (cash) — clearing the liability; the amount is HARD-CAPPED at the available pool (collected − already distributed, bounded by the 2300 GL outstanding) so tips can never be over-paid (TIP_OVER_DISTRIBUTE). 2300 always reconciles to what is still owed to staff. SoD: distributing is a manager/finance duty (order_mgt/exec), segregated from the cashier who rings sales (pos_sell) — a cashier cannot pay tips to themselves (403).","Prev/Det","Automated","Per period / per payout","Store Ops Mgr / Controller","P10/P16",
    "restaurant/tip.service.ts (pool/distribute/list, outstanding2300 reconciliation, over-distribute guard); restaurant.controller.ts (tips/pool|distribute|list; distribute @order_mgt/exec); schema/restaurant.ts tip_distributions + tip_distribution_lines + migration 0146; payments.tip → 2300 on checkout; cutover/tips.ts (ToE)","Inspect the pool computation, the 2300↔collected reconciliation, the over-distribute cap, and the cashier-vs-manager SoD on the distribute route.","Re-perform: ring sales with tips (2300 accrues), a cashier's distribute → 403, a manager distributes by hours (Dr 2300 / Cr 1000, 2300 clears to 0, shares correct), a second over-distribute → TIP_OVER_DISTRIBUTE; trial balance balanced (re-performed by the tips harness).","Tip distribution register; 2300 reconciliation","Implemented")
add("REV-18","Revenue & Cash","Application","Accounts Receivable; Bad-debt expense; Allowance for Doubtful Accounts (1190)","AR is carried at gross with no provision for expected credit losses — receivables that are partly/wholly uncollectible are overstated (assets/equity overstated, bad-debt expense understated and untimely), and a single person could both set the provision and post it (manage earnings via the allowance).","Valuation/Authorization",
    "AR Allowance for Doubtful Accounts (ECL): a periodic, aging-driven provision — each open-AR bucket (current / 1-30 / 31-60 / 61-90 / 91-120 / 120+) carries a loss rate and the allowance = Σ(outstanding × rate) (a flat-percentage method is also supported). Computation upserts an UNPOSTED row (one per tenant/as-of-date); posting is MAKER-CHECKED — the poster must DIFFER from the computer (computer self-post → SOD_SELF_POST, binds even Admin) — and journals only the DELTA vs the prior posted allowance (increase: Dr 5720 Bad-Debt Expense / Cr 1190 contra-asset; decrease reverses) so 1190 carries the cumulative provision while 1100 gross AR is untouched. Posting routes through LedgerService.postEntry, so it respects the period lock (PERIOD_LOCKED) and a posted allowance can't be re-posted (ALREADY_POSTED).","Det/Prev","Auto+Manual","Period-end","AR / Controller","P10/P16",
    "finance/ar-allowance.service.ts (computeAllowance aging buckets/rates; postAllowance delta + SoD computer≠poster); finance.controller.ts (/api/finance/ar-allowance/compute|:id/post|GET, gated creditors/ar/gl_post/exec); schema/ar-allowance.ts ar_allowance + migration 0166; COA 1190; cutover/basics.ts (ToE)","Inspect the aging-bucket rates, the allowance computation, the delta posting (Dr 5720 / Cr 1190), and the compute-vs-post SoD.","Re-perform: compute an allowance over seeded aged AR (buckets × rates → allowance), the computer's self-post → SOD_SELF_POST, a different user posts the delta → 5720/1190 move by the provision, a re-post → ALREADY_POSTED (re-performed by the basics harness).","AR allowance register; provision JE; SoD test","Implemented")
add("REV-19","Revenue & Cash","Application","Revenue; Contract Liability / Deferred Revenue (2410); Refund Liability (2420)","Service/subscription/project revenue is recognized in the wrong period — booked up-front (or never deferred) instead of as the performance obligations are satisfied, and a multi-element contract's price is not split by standalone selling price — so revenue and the contract-liability are misstated (TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 non-compliance; revenue overstated/understated, deferred revenue mis-carried, expected refunds unprovided).","Accuracy/Cutoff/Completeness/Valuation",
    "TFRS 15 / IFRS 15 five-step revenue recognition engine (the 'real ERP' deferred-revenue model; the restaurant POS keeps immediate recognition). A contract carries one or more performance obligations; the transaction price is ALLOCATED across them in proportion to standalone selling price (allocateBySSP — Σ allocated == total_price EXACTLY, the rounding residual lands on the largest-SSP PO; Σssp≤0 → INVALID_ALLOCATION). On activation the full price raises the contract liability (Dr 1100 AR / Cr 2410 Deferred Revenue, viaSubledger so the AR control is respected). buildSchedule lays out the recognition plan — over_time POs straight-line their allocated price across the months start..end, point_in_time POs a single row at the satisfaction date — and is idempotent (rebuilds only UNRECOGNIZED rows; recognized rows are never touched). recognize() releases revenue for all schedule rows due in/through a period (Dr 2410 / Cr 4300 Recognized Revenue), marks the row + bumps the PO satisfied_pct/status, and is idempotent (an already-recognized row is skipped — no double post). accrueRefundLiability provisions expected returns (Dr 4300 contra revenue / Cr 2420 Refund Liability) posting only the DELTA vs the prior provision. All posting routes through LedgerService.postEntry so the period lock (PERIOD_LOCKED, GL-15/16) and the GL-17 audit trail bind; recognition is tenant-scoped (HQ/Admin must name a tenant → TENANT_REQUIRED).","Prev","Automated","Per contract / period-end","Revenue Accountant / Controller","P10/P13",
    "revenue/revrec.service.ts (createContract; allocateBySSP residual handling; activate Dr1100/Cr2410; buildSchedule straight-line/point-in-time idempotent; recognize Dr2410/Cr4300; accrueRefundLiability delta Dr4300/Cr2420); revenue/revrec.controller.ts (/api/revenue/contracts POST|GET|:id|:id/allocate|:id/schedule|:id/activate|recognize|:id/refund-liability, gated exec/ar/fin_report); schema/revrec-contracts.ts rev_contracts/performance_obligations/revrec_schedules/refund_liability + migration 0172; COA 2410/2420; cutover/revrec.ts (ToE)","Inspect the SSP allocation (sums exactly to price), the activation/recognition/refund postings, the straight-line vs point-in-time schedule, and the idempotency + period-lock + tenant-scoping guards.","Re-perform: create a contract (total 1000, SSP 800 over_time / 400 point_in_time) → allocate sums to 1000 with residual on the larger PO; activate → Dr1100/Cr2410 1000; build schedule (4+1 rows); recognize 2040-01 → 2410 falls 500 / 4300 rises 500; recognize again → 0 new; refund liability 10% → Dr4300/Cr2420 50 (re-performed by the revrec harness).","Contract register; SSP allocation; deferred-revenue roll-forward; recognition + refund JEs","Implemented")

