add("INV-05","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","A branch stock-out is fulfilled by BUYING new stock while a sibling branch holds idle surplus (capital tied up / over-ordering); or stock is moved between branches without attribution or segregation of duties.","Existence/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Branch-aware replenishment routes transfer-before-buy: a low (branch,item) is first covered by an inter-branch TRANSFER from a sibling branch with surplus (tenant-scoped branch_stock move + branch-attributed cust_stock_log, executed under the warehouse-custody duty), and only the residual the transfers cannot cover raises a purchase requisition through the maker-checker buy flow (EXP-03). Transfer execution (wh_custody) is segregated from PR/PO approval (procurement / approvals).","Prev/Det","Auto+Manual","Per replenishment run","Planner / Warehouse / Procurement","P10/P13",
    "wms/replenishment.service.ts (suggest transfer/buy split, autoTransfer, autoPr); wms.controller.ts (auto-transfer @wh_custody vs auto-pr @procurement); schema branch_stock + item_supplier + migration 0130; cutover/wms.ts (ToE)","Inspect transfer-before-buy allocation, branch attribution, and leg segregation.","Deplete branch A below its reorder point with surplus at branch B -> suggest splits into a transfer (from B) + a buy (residual); auto-transfer moves branch_stock and logs both branches; auto-PR raises a PR for the residual; branch_stock reconciles (re-performed by the harness).","Branch replenishment run log; inter-branch transfer log; residual PR","Implemented")
add("INV-06","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS","Perpetual stock VALUE drifts from the GL inventory control account; receipts/issues/adjustments uncosted or not posted to GL → inventory & COGS misstated.","Existence/Valuation/Completeness",
    "Perpetual valued sub-ledger (inv_moves / inv_balances): every receipt/issue/adjustment updates the item's cost (moving-average, or FIFO/FEFO cost layers in inv_cost_layers) AND posts a balanced JE (Dr/Cr 1200 Inventory ↔ 2000 AP / 5000 COGS / 5810 variance). Reconciliation ties sub-ledger value to GL 1200; posting is idempotent on ref (no double-count); negative stock is blocked. FEFO consumes soonest-expiry layers first (perishable waste control). The sub-ledger and the costing module (FIFO/AVG/STD) are mutually exclusive per item (CONFLICTING_COSTING guard on both sides) so inventory is never double-capitalized to 1200.","Prev+Det","Automated","Per txn","Controller / Warehouse","P10",
    "inventory-ledger.service.ts; stock-ops.service.ts (bridge); 0131 inv_moves/inv_balances; 0132 inv_cost_layers (FIFO/FEFO); ledger.postEntry","Walkthrough receipt→issue→adjust + a stock-ops issue/transfer/stocktake on a tracked item, in both moving-avg and FEFO: inspect cost recompute / layer consumption, the balanced JE, and reconcile().","Sample receipt/issue/adjust + stock-ops moves → sub-ledger value ties to GL 1200 (reconciled); FEFO COGS = actual layer cost; over-issue blocked; duplicate ref deduped.","Reconciliation report; layers report; basics + compliance + stock-ops harness","Implemented")
add("INV-07","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS","Stock written off the books without independent review — one person posts a shrinkage/spoilage write-off to conceal a shortage they caused (theft of inventory).","Authorization",
    "Inventory write-off maker-checker (SoD): a NEGATIVE ad-hoc stock adjustment (a write-off) on POST /api/inventory/adjustments is a REQUEST that posts NOTHING — no variance JE, no FIFO/FEFO layer consumption, no balance change — until a DIFFERENT wh_adjust holder approves (POST /api/inventory/writeoffs/:id/approve). On approval the real valued adjustment runs atomically against current state (Dr 5810 / Cr 1200). Self-approval → SOD_VIOLATION (binds even Admin); one write-off pending per item/location; reject leaves stock untouched. A positive adjustment (overage/found) and a stocktake count-variance (the count is itself the authorizing document) post immediately and are out of scope.","Prev","Automated","Per write-off","Warehouse / Controller","P10",
    "inventory-ledger.service.ts requestWriteOff/approveWriteOff/rejectWriteOff/listWriteOffs; inventory-ledger.controller.ts (writeoffs/:id/approve|reject, wh_adjust); schema/inventory.ts inv_writeoff_requests + migration 0136; cutover/basics.ts + compliance.ts (ToE)","Inspect the request→approve flow + the approver≠requester check + that the request posts nothing until approval.","Re-perform: request a write-off (on-hand unchanged), attempt self-approve (SOD_VIOLATION), approve as a different user; confirm the variance JE + balance move only after approval (re-performed by the harnesses).","Write-off request register + SoD test","Implemented")
add("INV-08","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","Stock mis-located or stored beyond a bin's physical capacity — overflow held in an unrecorded location, breaking the perpetual location records and concealing where inventory physically is (loss / shrink risk; inaccurate pick paths).","Completeness; Accuracy",
    "Bin-capacity / location integrity: every storage bin carries a physical position + size + capacity, and putaway (POST /api/wms/putaway) enforces it — a receipt that would fill a bin past its defined capacity is rejected (422 BIN_CAPACITY_EXCEEDED) and no bin_stock moves. Bins without a capacity are unconstrained (back-compat). The warehouse layout (GET /api/wms/layout) reports live utilisation (on-hand ÷ capacity) and flags over-capacity bins; GET /api/wms/locate gives the exact bin(s) holding any item for spatial control.","Prev","Automated","Per putaway","Warehouse","P10",
    "wms.service.ts putaway (capacity guard) / warehouseLayout / locateItem / setBinLayout; wms.controller.ts (layout, locate, bins/:code/layout); schema/wms.ts bins.pos_*/dim_*/capacity + migration 0138; cutover/wms.ts (ToE)","Inspect the putaway capacity guard + the layout utilisation/locate read model.","Re-perform: set a bin capacity, putaway within capacity (accepted), putaway beyond it (422 BIN_CAPACITY_EXCEEDED, stock unchanged); confirm layout reports utilisation and locate finds the item (re-performed by the wms harness).","Bin capacity test + layout/locate read","Implemented")
add("INV-09","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","Available-to-promise mis-stated by leaked stock reservations — allocations that are never released or consumed accumulate so ATP drifts permanently low (false stock-outs), or a reservation oversells stock it never had.","Accuracy; Completeness",
    "ATP reservation integrity: stock reservations carry a lifecycle Open -> Fulfilled (goods shipped/issued) | Cancelled (order released), and ATP nets only OPEN reservations. allocate() is idempotent per (tenant, ref_doc, item) -- re-reserving the same document adjusts the one open row rather than stacking duplicates (a retried order cannot leak the float) -- and the additional reservation may not exceed current ATP (INSUFFICIENT_ATP), so a reservation can never oversell. release() frees a cancelled order's reservation back to ATP; fulfill() retires a shipped reservation from the open pool (the on-hand reduction is posted by the issue path, so the swap is ATP-neutral and never double-counted). A register exposes every reservation for review.","Prev","Automated","Per reservation","Planner / Warehouse","P10",
    "costing/atp.service.ts allocate (idempotent + ATP guard) / releaseAllocation / fulfillAllocation / listAllocations / atp (nets Open only); costing.controller.ts (allocate, allocations/:ref/release|fulfill, allocations); schema/costing.ts stock_allocations.status; cutover/costing.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reservation lifecycle + that ATP nets only Open + the idempotency/over-reserve guards.","Re-perform: allocate (ATP drops), re-allocate same ref (idempotent -- no leak), over-reserve (422 INSUFFICIENT_ATP), release (frees ATP), fulfill + on-hand drop (ATP-neutral) (re-performed by the costing harness).","Reservation register + ATP drift test","Implemented")
add("INV-10","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; Waste/scrap loss","Kitchen/ingredient waste is invisible — spoilage/over-production is not captured, so food-cost loss can't be measured or controlled; OR a perpetual-tracked item is written off as 'waste' to bypass the independent write-off approval (INV-07).","Completeness/Accuracy/Authorization",
    "Waste / spoilage logging with a write-off boundary: POST /api/inventory/waste records reason-coded ingredient waste (damage/expiry/spoilage/overproduction/prep_error/other), decrements the ingredient stock (customer_inventory + cust_stock_log) and, when a unit cost is supplied, posts Dr 5810 Scrap/Waste Loss / Cr 1200 Inventory (idempotent per WASTE- doc — mirrors recipe COGS, which credits 1200 on consumption). A by-reason analytics view (total cost, cost per reason) is the food-cost lever. **Boundary control:** a PERPETUAL-tracked item (an inv_balances row) is REJECTED here (USE_WRITEOFF) and must go through the INV-07 maker-checker write-off — so no one can dodge the independent write-off approval by mislabelling shrinkage as 'waste', and inventory value is never decremented twice.","Det/Prev","Automated","Per waste event","Kitchen / Warehouse / Controller","P10/P13",
    "inventory/waste.service.ts logWaste (perpetual-item guard, GL 5810/1200, stock decrement) + list (by-reason analytics); waste.controller.ts (/api/inventory/waste, warehouse/pos/order_mgt); schema/portal.ts waste_log + migration 0149; cutover/waste.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reason-coded capture + the 5810/1200 GL on costed waste + the perpetual-item USE_WRITEOFF boundary + the by-reason analytics.","Re-perform: costed waste posts Dr 5810 / Cr 1200 + decrements stock; uncosted waste logs with no GL; a perpetual-tracked item is rejected (USE_WRITEOFF); by-reason totals reconcile; trial balance balanced (re-performed by the waste harness).","Waste log + by-reason food-cost analytics","Implemented")

add("INV-11","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory; COGS","Theoretical-vs-actual food-cost variance is a single undifferentiated number — a manager sees that COGS ran over the recipe but not WHY or WHERE, so the over-usage can't be acted on (over-portioning vs spoilage vs theft go unaddressed and recur).","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Reason-coded food-cost variance review: each EOD-count variance (cust_variance — theoretical vs actual ingredient use, valued at cost) is tagged with a normalized reason_code (WASTE/OVERSTOCK/SPOILAGE/PORTIONING/THEFT/OTHER, enum-validated at POST /api/portal/variance) and an optional station. GET /api/menu/food-cost/variance values the variance at ingredient cost and rolls it up three ways — per ingredient (with High/Medium anomaly bands), by_reason and by_station — netting unfavourable/favourable, so 'Sauce station is 8% over theoretical (portioning) → retrain' is actionable. Yield/waste factors on the recipe BoM (INV-03) feed the theoretical baseline so the variance isn't inflated by un-costed trim loss. Tenant-scoped (RLS); read gated by exec/order_mgt.","Det","Auto+Manual","Per EOD count / weekly review","F&B Controller / Kitchen Mgr","P10/P13",
    "menu/food-cost.service.ts foodCostVariance (per-item + by_reason + by_station roll-ups, anomaly bands); portal.service.ts createVariance (persists reason_code/station); portal.controller.ts VarianceBody (reason_code enum); schema/bom.ts cust_variance.reason_code/station + migration 0161; /food-cost variance tab (by-reason/by-station tables); cutover/restaurant.ts (ToE)","Inspect the reason_code enum capture, the valued by_reason/by_station roll-ups, the anomaly bands, and tenant isolation.","Re-perform: seed counts with reason/station; the variance values per ingredient (NOODLE +฿30 High), nets +30/−50 to −20, by_reason PORTIONING +30 / WASTE −50, by_station Sauce +30 (20%); another tenant's counts are excluded (re-performed by the restaurant harness).","Reason-coded variance roll-up + by-station test","Implemented")

add("INV-12","Inventory & COGS","Application","Inventory","Per-branch reorder points are STATIC numbers — set once and never revisited — so a branch whose run-rate has grown carries too small a buffer and stocks out (lost sales), while a slow branch over-orders and ties up cash/spoils stock; neither is flagged.","Accuracy/Completeness",
    "Demand-driven par-level recommendation (layered on the INV-05 branch min-max + transfer-before-buy): for each (branch,item) the system derives the average daily usage from the trailing window of branch-tagged consumption (cust_stock_log Sale/Consume) and recommends reorder_point = ceil(avg_daily x lead_time_days x safety 1.25), flagging rows whose static reorder_point is below that demand-driven buffer (under_buffered). GET /api/replenishment/par-recommendations is read-only; a planner applies a recommendation per row (POST .../apply writes the reorder_point onto branch_stock, planner duty). lead_time_days is per (branch,item) (migration 0163). Tenant-scoped (RLS); gated planner/procurement.","Det","Auto+Manual","Periodic / per planning cycle","Planner / Supply Chain","P13",
    "wms/replenishment.service.ts parRecommendations (avg-daily-usage x lead x safety, under_buffered flag) + applyPar (writes reorder_point, planner); wms.controller.ts (/api/replenishment/par-recommendations[/apply]); schema/portal.ts branch_stock.lead_time_days + migration 0163; /replenishment par-recommendations section; cutover/wms.ts (ToE)","Inspect the avg-daily-usage derivation from consumption logs, the lead-time x safety reorder-point formula, the under_buffered flag, and the planner-gated apply.","Re-perform: seed branch consumption (10/day) at lead 3 -> recommend ROP 38 (under-buffered vs static 10); apply writes 38 onto branch_stock; tenant-isolated (re-performed by the wms harness).","Par recommendation list + apply test","Implemented")

